I'll calculate each financial ratio step by step using the provided financial statements.

## Step 1: Current Ratio
Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities
Current Ratio = $9,193,203.41 / $728,279.50 = 12.62

## Step 2: Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = ($2,545,589.48 / $5,565,589.48) × 100% = 45.74%

## Step 3: Debt to Asset Ratio
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets
Debt to Asset Ratio = $728,279.50 / $14,823,650.85 = 0.05

## Step 4: Net Profit Margin
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
Net Profit Margin = ($1,095,371.35 / $5,565,589.48) × 100% = 19.68%

## Step 5: Cash to Current Debt Ratio
Cash to Current Debt Ratio = (Cash on Hand + Bank Deposits) / Total Current Liabilities
Cash to Current Debt Ratio = ($4,303,451.63 + $2,938,804.13) / $728,279.50 = $7,242,255.76 / $728,279.50 = 9.94

## Step 6: Free Cash Flow (FCF)
FCF can be calculated from the cash flow statement as the Net Increase in cash
FCF = -$757,744.24

## Step 7: Return on Assets (ROA)
ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%
ROA = ($1,095,371.35 / $14,823,650.85) × 100% = 7.39%
